  "title": "Urgent - Freelance Transcriber (Kaki Bukit / Briefing on 4 Feb)",
  "description": "<ul><li>Location: Kaki Bukit (5-10mins walk from MRT Station)</li><li>Working Hours: 9:00am – 7:00pm (Flexi-timing)</li><li>Salary : Up to S$15 per hour (Depends on speed of process/typing)</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Complete the editing and verification of the transcripts of multi-speaker audio and video recordings in English and Mandarin / Malay / Tamil to support the development of automatic speech recognition models.</li><li>Ensure the annotated transcripts of all the annotators are at 95% accuracy and delivered within the specified timelines.</li><li>Ensure consistency of transcriptions and phonetic translations, in terms of the standardisation of word spelling and vocabulary</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Fast and accurate typing and word processing</li><li>Excellent listening and comprehension skills</li><li>Aptitude for discerning challenging audio and accented speech</li><li>Experience in annotation work will be a bonus</li><li>Knowledge of Singapore languages</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><br /></p><h1><em></em></h1>",
